This paper is about policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on convergence rate bounds for a suite of algorithms used in reinforcement learning. Given this focus, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could place it in categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
